himself named for his uncle Gen. Selah Hart of Kensington."}],"artworks":[],"tags":["ohio_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Married Mary Thompson by Justice Corner, 1826","body":"He removed from the family's Watertown home to Marion, Morgan County, Ohio with his parents in 1821, then married Mary Thompson, daughter of Hugh, on February 23, 1826 at Marion. The ceremony was performed by George Corner, Justice of the Peace. He farmed at Marion for the rest of his life and had eight children."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"short":"Andrews, Genealogical History of Deacon Stephen Hart (1875)","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/25/Geneological_history_of_Deacon_Stephen_Hart_and_his_descendants%2C_1632._1875%2C_%28IA_geneologicalhist01andr%29.pdf"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"selah-hart-jr-1797"},"I01256":{"id":"I01256","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Mary","last_name":"Hart","married_names":["Hart"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Mary Hart","maiden":"Thompson","display":"Mary Thompson Hart"},"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1802,"month":1,"day":24,"county":"Morgan","state":"Ohio","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_name":"Hugh Thompson"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H01496","date_year":1826,"date_month":2,"date_day":23,"location_city":"Marion","location_county":"Morgan","location_state":"Ohio","location_country":"United States","officiant":"Geo. Corner, Justice of the Peace","end_type":"death_of_sp